The paper presents a new approach to topic modeling that extends traditional models by learning a factorized latent variable representation. This approach has benefits traditionally associated with both discriminative and generative models. The paper also evaluates the model on classification tasks using convolutional neural network features. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of convolutional neural network features suggests a possible association with computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well.
